This paper deals with the privacy and security implications of drones equipped with video cameras. The paper discusses methods to detect whether a drone's camera is directed towards a target in real-time, which involves analyzing the encrypted FPV channel transmitted from the drone. This work involves aspects of computer security (cs.CR), computer vision (cs.CV), multimedia (cs.MM), human-computer interaction (cs.HC), and systems and control (cs.SY).
